message.content: cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. The paper deals with visual question answering (VQA) and proposes a new benchmark task called inverse VQA (iVQA) which requires better understanding of the image to generate a question that corresponds to a given image and answer pair. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a reinforcement learning framework to diagnose existing VQA models, which involves machine learning (cs.AI), deep learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
